<!--
VOICING PLAN:
- M1 (Eb Cm): open 4-note LH Eb2-Bb2-Eb3-G3; RH 2-note light opening
- M2 (Fm Bb Eb): LH tracks root down — full Fm4, Bb3, Eb3 open voicings
- M5 (Bb Cm¹): ⑤ 4-note Bb + ⑥¹ "43" Cm first inversion for variety
- M7 (Ab Gm): LH goes to full Ab2-Eb3-Ab3-C4 (4-note open IV)
- M8 (Bb²): ⑤² second inversion creates suspension into verse 2
- M11 (Ab Gm Ab): ④ full 4-note Ab + ③ Gm + ④ return — phrase peak
- M13 (EbΔ7): RH "333" G5-D5-Bb4 climax — highest pitch in arrangement
- M15 (Eb Bb¹): ⑤¹ first inversion for descending resolution
- M16: ① "334" Eb full close with Eb1 pedal

VOICE LEADING:
- M4→5: Eb common in RH and LH (Bb chord uses common F3 with Fm)
- M9→10: Bb4 common RH note from ① to ⑥
- M13: EbΔ7 — RH goes to G5 (highest note) — climax peak
- LH pedal faithfully tracks roots through 3-flat key

TEXTURE ARC:
- M1-4: 2-note RH, 3-4 note LH — quiet opening
- M5-8: growing; ⑤² suspension at M8 creates yearning
- M9-12: full through-composed middle — Ab 4-note LH
- M13-14: climax — ①Δ7 RH reaches G5; long ① holds
- M15-16: settle, "⑤¹" leads to final root position with pedal Eb1
-->
